The _suggested alternative_ provided by the compiler is its best guess of what identifier you wanted, assuming that what you typed is a misspelling (typo).  In your case, though, the identifier is correct but the proper header was not included.  You do not want to change the name of the function you are calling.

[`GetProcessIdOfThread`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/processthreadsapi/nf-processthreadsapi-getprocessidofthread) is defined in the `processthreadsapi.h` header, so you need to add

    #include &lt;processthreadsapi.h&gt;

to your source file.

